      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I agree that it would have to be an arbitrary value but i don\u0027t want to see someone to configure a tolerance for 23839 wrong readings in a row.\n\nIf that is what they think is best, why not?\n\nIf we pick 16 someone will say that isn\u0027t good enough... what value makes people happy?  I think it is best to not be a nanny.\n\n(I\u0027ve had to deal with a very similar thing here where the post code daemon decided to put a maximum number of post codes at something like 255 and it took months to get a higher maximum value allowed).",
