      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T17:30:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If we pick 16 someone will say that isn\u0027t good enough...\n\n16 would work well for me.\n\n\u003e (I\u0027ve had to deal with a very similar thing here where the post code \ndaemon decided to put a maximum number of post codes at something like \n255 and it took months to get a higher maximum value allowed).\n\nThat\u0027s a people problem you are describing though, not a technical problem with the limit itself.\n\nIn case someone needs to ignore a higher number of garbage readings they simply adjust the threshold.\n\nOtherwise it would be possible to configure a completely dead sensor which has lots of thresholds but cannot assert one in a reasonable time-frame.\n\nI\u0027m somewhat on the side of preventing misconfiguration because misconfiguration has caused my own contributions to be delayed and having loose schemas like that demands more effort from the reviewer.",
      "parentUuid": "f4dd72ad_ff4d8488",
      "revId": "04c396b77a8561c54fe53228dc15b5b960a578f6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
