      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is 23839 a technically wrong value or just a likely not intended value?  If it is a wrong value, sure give me a limit above which everything else is a wrong value.  If it is a \"likely not intended value\" it isn\u0027t known if it is a misconfiguration or not.  You\u0027re being a nanny.\n\n\u003e In case someone needs to ignore a higher number of garbage readings they simply adjust the threshold.\n\nI don\u0027t know how this is any different than the example I gave you.  It was a \"simple matter of updating a meson.options\".  Except it took months to get a change approved.  It doesn\u0027t matter if it is a \"technical problem\" or a \"people problem\" to me.  Why put ourselves through it?\n\n\u003e Otherwise it would be possible to configure a completely dead sensor which has lots of thresholds but cannot assert one in a reasonable time-frame.\n\nIf we can come up with some \"reasonable [maximum] time-frame\"... ok.  Let\u0027s express it in terms of that then.",
